            aside.notes.
              Kangaroo mother care: is a method invented for the Doctor Edgar Rey Sanabria where baby is carried by the mother with skin to skin contact 24 hr a day. The baby is held in a strict up-right position, between the mother’s breasts and under her clothes. Mothers are employed as “incubators” and as the main source of food and stimulation.



